name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Lutheran Church-Good Shepherd 1601 North Street SE, Olympia WA, 98501
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a Pfizer clinic at Lutheran Good Shepherd located at 1601 North Street SE, Olympia WA, 98501. The clinic is from 2:00 - 4:00PM. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 5401 Leary Avenue Northwest STE 202, Seattle WA, 98107
info: ***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** Insured, medicaid, medicare, and uninsured options all available. Walk-in's welcome, but will be advised to fill out information via this same sign up via kiosk. We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine. ****Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place above the nail salon. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. ~~~We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine.~~~ Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info: ***Joints for Jabs for any state resident AND $50 VISA Gift Card. THE GIFT CARD IS FOR WA RESIDENTS ONLY! IF YOU ARE AN OUT OF STATE STUDENT AS LONG AS YOU HAVE A WA ADDRESS. In conjunction with Apex Cannabis, this is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine or the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine*** This clinic is located at Apex Cannabis at 1325 N. Division St., Suite 103. Please enter the building at the time of your appointment only. ***You will receive a free joint of your choice up to a $30 value with your vaccination AND a $50 VISA gift Card whether it’s your first or 2nd dose. If you pre-register for your appointment you will also receive 30% off your purchase that day and if you are a walk-in appointment you’ll receive 15% off your purchase that day. ***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID and be 21 or over to enter the building*** *VERY IMPORTANT* ***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic**
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
